    rationale: "Spider angiomas, palmar erythema, and scleral icterus are physical stigmata of chronic liver disease. The most critical preoperative labs are LFTs (to quantify hepatocellular damage and synthetic function) and coagulation studies (PT/INR), because the liver synthesizes clotting factors I, II, V, VII, IX, X. Coagulopathy significantly affects surgical bleeding risk and anesthetic management. Albumin reflects synthetic function and affects drug protein binding. Pancreatitis labs are relevant if abdominal symptoms are present but are not the priority here. Thyroid and cortisol testing are not indicated by these findings.",
