    rationale: "Regional anesthesia (spinal or epidural) for hip replacement avoids systemic administration of volatile anesthetics, high-dose opioids, and benzodiazepines \u2014 all of which are deliriogenic, particularly in patients with pre-existing dementia. Maintaining the patient's consciousness and orientation during the procedure also reduces the disorientation associated with emergence from general anesthesia. Regional anesthesia does not eliminate postoperative pain management needs (though it reduces opioid requirements). It does not provide superior muscle relaxation for surgical exposure. The mechanism of delirium prevention is avoidance of deliriogenic agents, not pain signal blockade per se.",
