    rationale: "When a patient lacks decision-making capacity and no MPOA or family is available, the appropriate steps are: (1) attempt to identify next of kin or any legal surrogate, (2) involve the institutional ethics committee, and (3) if the procedure is urgent and delay would cause harm, proceed under the principle of beneficence with documentation. The emergency exception applies to truly emergent, life-threatening situations \u2014 a hip fracture requiring urgent (not emergent) surgery requires more deliberate process. Indefinite delay is inappropriate if the patient's condition will deteriorate. The anesthesia provider cannot serve as surrogate \u2014 this is a conflict of interest.",
    metadata: { topic: "informed-consent", priority: "high" },
