    rationale: "Isolated calf DVT is not benign. Approximately 20\u201330% of untreated calf DVTs propagate proximally to the popliteal or iliofemoral veins, substantially increasing PE risk. In a patient undergoing major orthopedic surgery \u2014 a high-risk procedure for VTE \u2014 the decision to anticoagulate or delay surgery requires careful risk-benefit analysis. Current guidelines generally recommend anticoagulation for symptomatic calf DVT, with consideration of the surgical timeline. Dismissing calf DVT as inconsequential is clinically inappropriate. The decision is not limited to patients with prior PE history.",
