    prompt: "A CRNA is performing a preoperative assessment on a 72-year-old man scheduled for elective inguinal hernia repair. During the interview, the patient repeatedly asks for questions to be repeated and responds to verbal instructions with a puzzled expression. The whisper test reveals he cannot hear a whispered voice at 2 feet. What is the most important perioperative implication of this finding?",
